casebody.data:
STATE EX REL. Willie PRICE
v.
STATE of Louisiana NO. 2017-KH-0305 Supreme Court of Louisiana. May 18, 2018

Not considered. Relator has not demonstrated that he sought review in the court of appeal before filing in this Court nor shown the "extraordinary circumstances" that would justify bypassing that level of review. La.S.Ct.R. X § 5(b).
